  </figure>
  </p>

    

</header>
  <div data-component="article-content">



            <p>Never Grave: The Witch and The Curse has finally got a release date. Announced during tonight's State of Play event, the side scrolling action game will be coming out on the 5th March, 2026 on the PS5 and PS4.</p>
<p>Developed by Frontside 180 and published as part of Pocketpair's relatively new video game publishing arm, the game received a new gameplay trailer as part of the announcement.</p>
<p>This trailer not only shows off a few new boss fights, but also an equipment screen, what appears to be a skill tree, and some fancy magically-charged combat. You can watch it yourself below.</p>

<figure>
<p>
<a aria-label="Never Grave: The Witch and The Curse - Release Date Announcement Trailer | PS5 &amp; PS4 Games" data-platform="youtube" href="https://www.youtube.com/embed/61ZdeqZAy2M?autoplay=1" onclick="((e) => { e.preventDefault(); e.currentTarget.closest('.video_wrapper').innerHTML = e.currentTarget.querySelector('template').innerHTML; enableElements(); })(event)" title="Click to play video from YouTube">
<span>Never Grave: The Witch and The Curse - Release Date Announcement Trailer | PS5 &amp; PS4 Games</span>
<template>
<iframe allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen="" data-src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/61ZdeqZAy2M?autoplay=1" frameborder="0" loading="lazy" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/61ZdeqZAy2M?autoplay=1" title="Never Grave: The Witch and The Curse - Release Date Announcement Trailer | PS5 &amp; PS4 Games">
</iframe> </template>
</a>
</p>
<figcaption>Watch the new trailer for Never Grave: The Witch and The Curse here. <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=61ZdeqZAy2M" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Watch on YouTube</a></figcaption></figure>


<p>Frontside 180, a fully-owned subsidiary of Pocketpair, dropped a Steam demo for Never Grave in January 2024. Since then, it's been cooking away in the background. It's the second game to come from Pocketpair's publishing arm, <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/palworld-studio-pocketpair-wont-publish-games-with-ai-we-dont-believe-in-it">which Pocketpair staff have said will not work with games using AI, NFTs, or Web 3</a>.</p><p>

The first game to come from Pocketpair Publishing was Dead Take, which is a fantastic indie project <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/surgent-studios-reveals-full-cast-for-dead-take-including-sam-lake-jane-perry-and-laura-bailey">starring popular voice actors Ben Starr, Neil Newbon, and others.</a></p><p>Never Grave: The Witch and The Curse certainly looks charming. Here's hoping Frontside 180 can magic away the months so March comes all the quicker.</p>

