            <p>
Sonic Racing: CrossWorlds is set to receive three new free Sega characters over the next few months.
</p>
<p>
The first, coming next month, is NiGHTS from the iconic Sega Saturn game. Though not officially announced by Sega previously, the <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/sonic-racing-crossworlds-leak-reveals-more-iconic-characters-coming-to-its-roster-which-retro-fans-will-love">character is present on the back of the physical version of the game</a>, so their inclusion has been known since before the game's release. Still, at least we know they're coming in December.
</p>
<p>
NiGHTS will be followed by <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/super-monkey-ball">Super Monkey Ball</a>'s AiAi, the cute little banana-grabbing monkey who's been let out of their ball. AiAi will join in January 2026.
</p>

<figure>
<p>
